# ARCA Prototype API — Reusable, versioned requests
# Use with: VS Code REST Client extension, or run scripts/test_api.sh for curl-based tests
# Start backend: cd arca-prototype && uvicorn backend.main:app --port 8000
# Variables: ARCA_CUIT, ARCA_PASSWORD from .env (or override @cuit, @password below)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@cuit = 20268448536
@password = {{$dotenv ARCA_PASSWORD}}

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### --- Representados (Comunicaciones de mis representados) ---

### GET representados from cache
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/representados?cuit={{cuit}}

### POST fetch representados from ARCA
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/representados
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cuit": "{{cuit}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### --- Notifications (cache) ---

### GET notifications from SQLite cache (no ARCA call)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/notificaciones-contenido?cuit={{cuit}}

### POST fetch from ARCA and save to cache
# Add "cuit_representado": "30712461221" for comunicaciones de mis representados (e.g. ALL ONLINE SOLUTIONS)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/notificaciones-contenido
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cuit": "{{cuit}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### --- PDF attachments ---

### GET PDF from cache (notification 582958952 = SCT Intimación)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/notificaciones/582958952/pdf?cuit={{cuit}}

### POST upload PDF to store in SQLite
# Prereq: notification must exist in cache (run POST notificaciones-contenido first)
# Replace path with actual PDF file (relative to this file)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/attachments/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="cuit"

{{cuit}}
------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="notification_id"

582958952
------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="SCT-Intimacion.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./data/attachments/SCT-Intimacion.pdf
------FormBoundary--

### POST download PDF attachment via DFE REST API
# Logs in, fetches notification detail to discover idArchivo, then GET /api/v1/communications/{id}/{idArchivo}
# id_archivo=0 triggers auto-discovery; or pass known ID (e.g. 587346976 for SCT Intimación)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/attachments/download
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cuit": "{{cuit}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "notification_id": 582958952,
  "id_archivo": 0,
  "filename": ""
}

### --- Libro IVA Digital ---

### GET generate from Mis Comprobantes (ventas)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/libro-iva/generate?cuit=30712461221&fecha_desde=2026-02-01&fecha_hasta=2026-02-29&tipo=ventas

### GET reconcile data (comprobantes + IVA breakdown)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/libro-iva/reconcile-data?cuit=30712461221&fecha_desde=2026-02-01&fecha_hasta=2026-02-29&tipo=ventas

### GET CSV template
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/libro-iva/template?tipo=ventas

### POST convert CSV to AFIP format (returns file)
# Use multipart: file=@path/to/ventas.csv, tipo=ventas
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/libro-iva/convert
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="tipo"

ventas
------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="ventas.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

fecha,tipo_comp,punto_venta,numero_desde,numero_hasta,cuit_contraparte,denominacion,importe_total,importe_neto,importe_iva
20260201,1,4,206682,206682,30123456789,EMPRESA EJEMPLO SRL,12100,10000,2100
------FormBoundary--

### POST convert preview (JSON, no download)
# Same as above but /convert-preview

### --- Other endpoints ---

### POST login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/arca/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "cuit": "{{cuit}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}
